    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-17T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-17T07:00:00-05:00" n="489"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363/10–1744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-17T15:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 17, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3967. ReDeptel 2443, October 16, 4 p.m.<note n="70" xml:id="d489fn70">See
                        footnote 69 above.</note> The Department’s attention is drawn to Iranian
                    press comment on Iranian Government’s refusal to accept Soviet request for oil
                    concessions in northern Iran reported in immediately preceding telegram.<note
                        n="71" xml:id="d489fn71">Telegram 3966, not printed.</note> This material
                    appeared in <hi rend="italic">Pravda</hi> for October 16 and in other Moscow
                    papers for October 17. Following customary Soviet press technique in such cases,
                    the citations selected undoubtedly express the Soviet attitude toward the
                    Iranian Government’s action and are an indication of Soviet dissatisfaction with
                    the Iranian Government’s decision.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tehran.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
